      "title": "Why Kroger Stock Dropped Today",
      "summary": "Kroger stock fell 8.43% after the supermarket operator's fiscal Q1 earnings missed expectations. Adjusted sales grew only 0.5% year-over-year to $46 billion, while gross margin declined to 22.7% from 23% due to higher shipping costs, price reductions, and labor expenses. CEO Greg Foran acknowledged that operating costs are growing faster than sales and pledged to reduce expenses, though the company maintains its full-year financial guidance.",
